{{Infobox organization |name = Wheat Research Centre |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = July 1980 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dinajpur]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.bari.gov.bd/ Wheat Research Centre] |remarks = }}
'''Wheat Research Centre''' is an autonomous national research institute that researches the production and cultivation of wheat in Bangladesh and is located in Nashipur, [[Dinajpur]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref name="wrc">{{cite web|last1=Islam|first1=Md Shahidul|title=Wheat Research Centre|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Wheat_Research_Centre|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=30 December 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fear of Fatal Fungal Disease: Wheat cultivation withheld in 8 dists|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/fear-fatal-fungal-disease-wheat-cultivation-withheld-8-dists-1309711|accessdate=30 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=5 November 2016|language=en}}</ref> Dr Naresh Chandra Dev Barma is the head of the centre.<ref>{{cite news|title=Global efforts to fight wheat blast|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/global-efforts-fight-wheat-blast-1454227|accessdate=30 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=26 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>
==History== Wheat Research Centre traces its origins to the Accelerated Wheat Research Programme for Bangladesh which was founded in 1971 and ended in June 1975. It was revived as the Expanded Wheat Research Programme. Wheat Research Centre was established on July 1980 under the [[Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute]]. It is one of six research centres under the Bangladesh Agricultural Research Institute. It has released wheats developed by [[International Maize and Wheat Improvement Center]]. From 1975 to 1985 wheat varieties released by the centre contributed to a 30 to 40 percent growth in wheat output in Bangladesh.<ref name="wrc"></ref> The centre is responsible for preventing wheat blast damage to corps and supporting farmers.<ref>{{cite news|title='Wheat blast' threatens yield|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/wheat-blast-threatens-yield-784372|accessdate=30 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=1 March 2016|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Wheat blast affects 15,500 hectares of land in 5 dists|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/country/wheat-blast-affects-15500-hectares-land-5-dists-1208944|accessdate=30 December 2017|work=The Daily Star|date=14 April 2016|language=en}}</ref>
